{"title_page": "The Boy and the Fog", "text_new": "{{short description|1953 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Boy and the Fog\n| image          =\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Roberto Gavald\u00f3n]]\n| producer       = [[Jes\u00fas Grovas]]\n| writer         = [[Edmundo B\u00e1ez]]<br>Roberto Gavald\u00f3n<br>[[Rodolfo Usigli]]\n| starring       = [[Dolores del R\u00edo]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Gabriel Figueroa\n| editing        = Gloria Schoemann\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|1953|12|24|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 111 minutes\n| country        = Mexico\n| language       = Spanish\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''The Boy and the Fog''''' ({{lang-es|'''El Ni\u00f1o y la niebla'''}}) is a 1953 Mexican [[drama film]] directed by [[Roberto Gavald\u00f3n]]. It was entered into the [[1954 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name=\"festival-cannes.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/3849/year/1954.html |title=Festival de Cannes: The Boy and the Fog |accessdate=29 January 2009|work=festival-cannes.com}}</ref>  \n\n==Plot==\nMarta ([[Dolores del R\u00edo]]) is a woman who lives obsessed, since her brother died of [[schizophrenia]] and her mother remains interned at a mental health hospital. Fearful that the disease is congenital, Marta keeps her family background secret from her husband while overprotecting her only son. Because of her obsession, Marta does not realize that the only psychologically affected in her family is her.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Dolores del R\u00edo]]\n* [[Alejandro Ciangherotti]] (as Alejandro Ciangherotti hijo)\n* [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Ferriz]]\n* [[Lupe Incl\u00e1n]]\n* [[Pedro L\u00f3pez Lagar]]\n* [[Tana Lynn]]\n* [[Eduardo Noriega (Mexican actor)|Eduardo Noriega]]\n* [[Carlos Riquelme]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|id=0046129|title=The Boy and the Fog}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boy And The Fog}}\n[[Category:1953 drama films]]\n[[Category:1953 films]]\n[[Category:Best Picture Ariel Award winners]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Roberto Gavald\u00f3n]]\n[[Category:Mexican black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Mexican films]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language films]]\n{{1950s-Mexico-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1953 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = The Boy and the Fog\n| image          =\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Roberto Gavald\u00f3n]]\n| producer       = [[Jes\u00fas Grovas]]\n| writer         = [[Edmundo B\u00e1ez]]<br>Roberto Gavald\u00f3n<br>[[Rodolfo Usigli]]\n| starring       = [[Dolores del R\u00edo]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Gabriel Figueroa\n| editing        = Gloria Schoemann\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{film date|1953|12|24|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 111 minutes\n| country        = Mexico\n| language       = Spanish\n| budget         = \n}}\n\n'''''The Boy and the Fog''''' ({{lang-es|'''El Ni\u00f1o y la niebla'''}}) is a 1953 Mexican [[drama film]] directed by [[Roberto Gavald\u00f3n]]. It was entered into the [[1954 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name=\"festival-cannes.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/archives/ficheFilm/id/3849/year/1954.html |title=Festival de Cannes: The Boy and the Fog |accessdate=29 January 2009|work=festival-cannes.com}}</ref>  \n\n==Plot==\nMarta ([[Dolores del R\u00edo]]) is a woman who lives obsessed, since her brother died of [[schizophrenia]] and her mother remains interned at a mental health hospital. Fearful that the disease is congenital, Marta keeps her family background secret from her husband while overprotecting her only son. Because of her obsession, Marta does not realize that the only psychologically affected in her family is her.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Dolores del R\u00edo]]\n* [[Alejandro Ciangherotti]] (as Alejandro Ciangherotti hijo)\n* [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Ferriz]]\n* [[Lupe Incl\u00e1n]]\n* [[Pedro L\u00f3pez Lagar]]\n* [[Tana Lynn]]\n* [[Eduardo Noriega (Mexican actor)|Eduardo Noriega]]\n* [[Carlos Riquelme]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|id=0046129|title=The Boy and the Fog}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Boy And The Fog}}\n[[Category:1953 drama films]]\n[[Category:1953 films]]\n[[Category:Best Picture Ariel Award winners]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Roberto Gavald\u00f3n]]\n[[Category:Mexican black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Mexican films]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language films]]\n{{1950s-Mexico-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Boy_and_the_Fog"}
